text: Year 102 (CII) was a common year starting on Saturday (link will display the full calendar) of the Julian calendar. At the time, it was known as the Year of the Consulship of Ursus and Sura (or, less commonly, year 855 Ab urbe condita). The name 102 has been used since the early medieval period, when the Anno Domini calendar era became the normal method in Europe for naming years. == Births == * == Deaths == * Ban Chao, Chinese general of the Han Dynasty (b. AD 32) * Clement I, bishop of Rome (approximate date) * Yin, Chinese empress of the Han Dynasty ==References==
